      "raw_text": "Work on the new Post street bridge\nOf the Washington Water Power COM\npany IL progressing rapidly, Just now\nattention being paid to the blasting\nOF rock to make room for the an\nchorage from the south, end Of the\narch. Big poles for making the false\nsupport for the new structure are on\nthe ground. Engineer Strack OF the\ncompany says that soon the work Of\ncutting away the corner Of the C. q G.\nmill, which II owned by the COM\npany, viii be commenced, It. being\nnecessary to take some eight feet on\nthe corner Of the building to make\nway for the width Of the new bridge\nrequired for the double tracks."
    }
